# On Arrays

An array is a rectangular collection of items arranged along 0 or more axes.
Each item of an array is an array itself. An array may be a single number or character. These
arrays are called simple scalars or elements. An array may be a list of zero or more items.
These arrays are called vectors. An array

An array all of whose items are elements is called a simple array.
Otherwise the the array is a nested array.   
     



